commit.message: Write each log on a new line

Persist the logs to a file

- Training the model takes hours and the ability to view all the logs
on screen is diminished, especially on a virtual machine on the cloud.
- Persist the logs to view how the training is progressing later
Close the file in case an exception doesn't happen
Fix some ommissions

Change save_checkpoint argument order

- non-default arguments have precedence over default arguments
Create a command line app to resume training from a file

Add ability to resume training for previously trained model

- Include epoch, hidden_units and dropout information when saving a
checkpoint. This information will help reconstruct state and resumee
from where the training stopped.
- Add a resume_training method to train a previously trained and
persisted model
- Change the dropout command argument to accept a list of space
separated values so that dropout rates can be defined for each hidden
layer
Add ability to specify dropout rates per hidden layer
Ignore custom .vscode settings folder
Update README
Update README and help text
Remove build information from dependency file
Create readme.md
Remove FloydHub references

Remove unused references

- Remove flower references because this is not a flower classifier
- Remove the test_nn command line option because the test folder is not
structured in a way to support this
Create file to generate final uploadable results
Update ignore list
Remove the "labels_path" command line option
Fix the predict command line interface
Fix the predict method

Polish up the code

- Use more elegant solution to create sub-folders inside train
- Persist the category-to-folder map
Bring the test folder back into the fray
Ignore training, validation and training datasets

Ignore checkpoint model files

- They tend to be large and we don't want them in version control
- Besides, they can be regenerated

Make updates to utils file

- Add trailing slash in train/valid/test folders to avoid ambiguity in
paths
- Remove zero increment to steps (what?). This line was causing the
validation to be run at every iteration and the training process became
slow as a result. With this fix, validation runs every 40 iterations
Remove floydhub files from version control
Create env dependency file
Include accidentally deleted lines
Create a terminal utility for training the model

Create a utility to group photo files

- This utility groups photo files into sub-folders based on category
labels
